      zh: {"term":"丢失更新异常","explanation":"并发异常之一。两个事务同时修改同一数据行，后提交的事务无视先提交事务所做的修改，直接进行覆盖，导致前者的修改丢失。"},
      en: {"term":"Lost Update Anomaly","explanation":"A concurrency problem where two transactions read the same data, modify it, and commit sequentially, with the second transaction overwriting the updates of the first."},
      my: {"term":"ပြင်ဆင်ချက် ပျောက်ဆုံးသွားမှု အမှား","explanation":"လုပ်ဆောင်ချက် နှစ်ခုက ဒေတာတစ်ခုတည်းကို တစ်ပြိုင်တည်းပြင်ရာတွင် နောက်မှပြီးသော လုပ်ဆောင်ချက်က ရှေ့ကပြင်ဆင်မှုကို ဖုံးအုပ်ဖျက်ဆီးလိုက်ခြင်း。","needsReview":true},
      vi: {"term":"Hiện tượng mất bản cập nhật","explanation":"Lỗi truy cập đồng thời khi hai giao dịch cùng sửa một dữ liệu, giao dịch hoàn tất sau ghi đè và làm mất thay đổi của giao dịch trước。","needsReview":true},
      fr: {"term":"Perte de mise à jour","explanation":"Anomalie de concurrence où deux écritures concurrentes se chevauchent, la seconde écrasant le travail de la première。","needsReview":true},
      aliases: ["Lost Update"],
      related: ["pessimistic_concurrency_control","optimistic_concurrency_control"],
      example: {"sql":"Using the Repeatable Read isolation level prevents certain lost update anomalies."},
      source: "project-glossary-v2",
      ko: { term: "갱신 손실 이상", explanation: "두 개의 트랜잭션이 동일한 데이터를 읽고 수정하여 순차적으로 커밋할 때, 나중에 커밋된 트랜잭션이 먼저 완료된 트랜잭션의 수정 사항을 덮어써서 유실시키는 동시성 이상 현상입니다." }
